# AI Chat System

AI Chat is different from AI Tutor.

It is a general-purpose assistant interface.

It does NOT enforce structured learning flows.

---

# Product Vision

AI Chat must:

- Answer general legal questions
- Provide explanations on demand
- Support free-form conversation
- Handle non-curriculum queries
- Route users to AI Tutor when needed

---

# Key Distinction

AI Tutor = structured learning system  
AI Chat = flexible assistant

Never merge both systems.

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

AIChatController (Riverpod)

↓

AIChatState

↓

AIService (Shared with Tutor)

↓

Context Router

↓

Optional RAG Layer

---

# State Management

AIChatState includes:

- idle
- loading
- streaming
- responding
- error

Core Data:

- messages
- chatThreads
- activeThread
- contextMode
- memoryEnabled

---

# Chat Modes

1. General Mode
2. Legal Q&A Mode
3. Study Support Mode
4. Explanation Mode

Each mode changes prompt behavior.

---

# Context Rules

AI Chat may optionally use:

- course context
- lesson context
- user history

But must never force structured learning.

---

# Memory System

Memory is optional in AI Chat.

Two modes:

- Ephemeral Chat (default)
- Persistent Chat (user enabled)

---

# Routing Logic

If query requires:

- structured learning → route to AI Tutor
- practice questions → route to Quiz Engine
- exams → route to Mock Exam system

---

# Offline Behaviour

AI Chat:

- disabled offline for generation
- may show cached responses

---

