---

# UI Composition Rules

AI Chat must include:

- chat input
- streaming messages
- mode selector
- thread history
- optional memory indicator

---

# UX Rules

- responses must be conversational
- avoid over-structuring
- allow interruptions
- support follow-up questions

---

# Safety Rules

AI must:

- avoid hallucinated legal claims
- distinguish opinion vs fact
- suggest verification when uncertain

---

# Performance

- first token < 500ms target
- streaming mandatory
- cancel previous requests on new input

---

# Accessibility

Must support:

- screen reader message streaming
- focus management
- readable message structure

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

Context Router

Chat State Manager

Thread handling

Widget Tests:

Chat UI

Thread UI

Mode switching

Integration Tests:

Full chat lifecycle

Routing between AI systems

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating AI Chat:

- always support multi-threading
- always support streaming responses
- always implement context routing
- never confuse with AI Tutor system